      "message": "I had similar in-progress code, so I\u0027m quite interested in this patch.\nIt\u0027s very close to what I had, and I can see that the bugs I found (CHAP authentication being broken, checking that the parent interface is actually an Ethernet interface, ...) are fixed here.\n\nMy local patches include changes to export more information in pppoeclient_dump. That\u0027s pretty straightforward, and seems like it\u0027d be generally useful (but can clearly be done in a follow-up commit).\n\nI\u0027ve also added an \u0027instance\u0027 field which makes the integration easier for us (in Netgate\u0027s TNSR). That\u0027s something that may or may not be generally applicable though.\n\nAdditionally, I have some basic python test code for my version of the pppoeclient plugin. I\u0027ll try to make that usable for this version instead.\n\nOne issue I see, unless I\u0027m missing something, is the pppox API call is not available. As far as I can see authentication can only be configured via the CLI, not via the API. So I think the pppox API call should be registered after all.",
