      "message": "Thanks, this was very helpful feedback.\n\nThe main issue you pointed out is fixed now:\n- the pppox auth API is registered and usable\n- pppoeclient_dump/details now exports a bit more runtime state as well, including pppox_sw_if_index, session_id and client_state\n- pppoeclient_dump also honors the sw_if_index filter now\n\nThe Ethernet parent-interface check and the CHAP authentication issue are also covered in the current patch set, and the result has been validated on a real PPPoE line.\n\nI did not add the instance field in this patch, because that seems more integration-specific and may be better handled separately if we decide it is generally useful upstream.\n\nIf your Python test code can be adapted cleanly to this version, that would be very useful as a follow-up as well.",
